# Quality And Structure

- Keep modules small, focused, and easy to reason about.
- Separate UI rendering, domain logic, data access, and ingestion concerns.
- Prefer composition over deep shared abstractions.
- Use folder structure that reflects product areas and technical boundaries clearly.
- Make high-impact logic easy to test and inspect.
- Avoid hidden side effects in transformation or reasoning code.
- Favor explicit data flow over magical conventions.
- When in doubt, choose the structure that makes trust-sensitive behavior easiest to audit.
